{{Quote|My people never saw his face when he struck&mdash;but they heard his voice. When my lord spoke, every living thing on Katarr died. The destruction of Katarr echoed through the Force, the screaming of countless lives.|[[Visas Marr]]|<ref name="Unseen, Unheard">{{Tales|24|Unseen, Unheard}}</ref>}}
The '''Conclave at Katarr''' was an event of the [[Old Sith Wars]], occurring in [[3952 BBY]], and was the first major event of the [[First Jedi Purge]] that took place during that [[Dark Wars|time period]]. That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the last known hundred [[Jedi/Legends|members]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] secretly assembled on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Katarr/Legends|Katarr]], a colony of the [[Miraluka/Legends|Miraluka]] [[Species/Legends|species]], a race who saw through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Atris]] summoned the Jedi she had kept contact with to a secret meeting on Katarr, seemingly to discuss the future of the Jedi Order. Her real intention, however, was to use the Jedi as bait, hoping their shadowy adversaries would reveal themselves. She leaked information about the conclave, which [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Nihilus]] received.<ref name="Kotor II" />

[[File:Katarrdevastation.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The cities of Katarr in flames]]
Unfortunately for Katarr, Atris's plan backfired; the Jedi were not aware of the true extent of Nihilus' power. Nihilus arrived on Katarr before the meeting could begin and, using a unique variation of [[Force drain/Legends|Force drain]], he stripped the Force from Katarr's surface, [[Death/Legends|killing]] every living being on the planet. Of all its living denizens, [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]], flora and fauna, Nihilus spared only one Miraluka woman, [[Visas Marr]], who was subsequently recruited into the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] as Nihilus's [[Sith apprentice/Legends|apprentice]].<ref name="Kotor II" /> 3,933 [[19 BBY/Legends|years later]], the Jedi who survived [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]] that [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|succeeded]] in destroying the Jedi Order, attempted to draw the Sith into a trap, with the similarly disastrous [[Conclave on Kessel]].<ref name="Purge">[[Purge (comic book)|''Purge'']]</ref>

